Recommended Dataset:

Kaggle - House Prices: Advanced Regression Techniques

Link: https://www.kaggle.com/c/house-prices-advanced-regression-techniques

Description:

Contains 79 explanatory variables describing (almost) every aspect of residential homes in Ames, Iowa.

Ideal for regression models like Linear Regression, Random Forest, Gradient Boosting, and more.

Includes missing values, categorical and numerical variables â€” perfect for real-world modeling.



2. Alternative Datasets:

a. Ames Housing Dataset

Source: UCI Machine Learning Repository or Kaggle

Features: 2930 observations with 80+ features

Use Case: Advanced regression and feature engineering tasks


b. Boston Housing Dataset (not recommended for modern use due to ethical concerns)

Contains outdated and limited data.


c. Real Estate Valuation Data Set (UCI)

Link: https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/datasets/Real+estate+valuation+data+set

Region: Taiwan

Features: House age, distance to MRT station, number of convenience stores, etc.
